            <h2 class="title on-blog">New Documentation Site</h2>
            
        
            
<p>In preparation of the overhaul of our push service for the upcoming release of iOS 7 to the public,
we have reworked our documentation packaging to make it easier to browse.</p>

<!-- more -->

<p>If you find errors, typos and inaccuracy, you can contribute to it by sending us a pull request. The documentation repository is available on <a href="https://github.com/processone/developer.boxcar.io/">Github developer.boxcar.io Repository</a>.</p>

<p>Next step is to share our API example code if various languages and demo application on <a href="http://github.com">Github</a>.</p>

<p>Technical notes: The documentation is based on <a href="http://developer.github.com">Github Developer</a> site and is build using <a href="http://nanoc.ws">nanoc</a>.</p>


            
