<div class="entry" id="/blog/2014-09-11-push_cancel_api/">
  
<ul class="meta">
  <li class="published">
    <span class="octicon octicon-calendar"></span>
    September 11, 2014
    
  </li>
  <li class="who_when">
    <img height="20" width="20" src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a86897320f9fcda11c8ce08b3e3489f4?s=20&amp;d=https://a248.e.akamai.net/assets.github.com%2Fimages%2Fgravatars%2Fgravatar-user-420.png">
      <a href="https://github.com/mremond">mremond</a>
  </li>
</ul>

<h2 class="title">
  <a href="/blog/2014-09-11-push_cancel_api/">Publisher API endpoint to cancel running pushes</a>
</h2>
    
<p>The publisher API allows you send push notifications and send you back the <strong>push_id</strong> of the push being processed.</p>

<p>For long running pushes, it was frustrating that you could not cancel it while it was running. It was specially relevant 
if you made a mistake or typo in the push being send to million of devices.</p>

‚Ä¢¬†‚Ä¢¬†‚Ä¢ ¬†¬† <div class="read-more"><a href="/blog/2014-09-11-push_cancel_api/">Continue reading ‚Ä∫</a></div>
</div>

