  </li>
  <li class="who_when">
    <img height="20" width="20" src="https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=20&amp;d=https://a248.e.akamai.net/assets.github.com%2Fimages%2Fgravatars%2Fgravatar-user-420.png">
      <a href="https://github.com/jpcarlino">jpcarlino</a>
  </li>
</ul>

<h2 class="title">
  <a href="/blog/2014-07-24-boxcar-android-sdk-1/">Boxcar Android SDK 1.1.0.11</a>
</h2>
    
<p>Boxcar Framework v.1.1.0.11 makes the following changes:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Apache commons-codec removed as a dependency (isn‚Äôt needed anymore)</li>
  <li>Add more retries for UDID service query</li>
  <li>Allow developer to set username on each registration: do also discourage setting the username on framework initialization</li>
  <li>Wake-lock protect ‚Äòstart‚Äô method from boxcar api</li>
  <li>Wake-lock for push callback from 3rd party application: ensure device can‚Äôt go to sleep while application callback is being executed to notify about an incoming push</li>
  <li>Do use WakefulBroadcastReceiver for GCM: bypass GCMBroadcastReceiver class to replace it for a wakeful receiver. Use a custom implementation for GCMBaseIntentService that relies on the wake lock from the receiver instance instead of doing its own locking. This ensures the CPU from device can‚Äôt go to sleep while receiver is being executed.</li>
  <li>Play no sound if file name is unknown or blank in payload</li>
  <li>Allow developer to set a custom default sound</li>
  <li>Use the sound file defined on payload: if filename is present on payload and the resource is available on ‚Äòres/raw‚Äô folder, then we play it instead of the default notification sound</li>
  <li>Add 10.0.2.2 to the list of known hosts: this is the IP used by Android Emulator to access localhost</li>
</ul>

<p>The new SDK is available in developer download area.</p>

</div>

<p><br></p>
<hr>

<p><br></p>

