  <entry>
    <id>tag:developer.boxcar.io,2014-09-11:/blog/2014-09-11-push_cancel_api/</id>
    <title type="html">Publisher API endpoint to cancel running pushes</title>
    <published>2014-09-10T22:00:00Z</published>
    <updated>2014-09-10T22:00:00Z</updated>
    <author>
      <name>mremond</name>
      <uri>https://github.com/mremond</uri>
    </author>
    <link rel="alternate" href="http://developer.boxcar.io/blog/2014-09-11-push_cancel_api/">
    <content type="html">
&lt;p&gt;The publisher API allows you send push notifications and send you back the &lt;strong&gt;push_id&lt;/strong&gt; of the push being processed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For long running pushes, it was frustrating that you could not cancel it while it was running. It was specially relevant 
if you made a mistake or typo in the push being send to million of devices.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;!-- more --&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That‚Äôs why we introduced two new publisher API calls:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Cancelling a push notifications being sent, by its push id&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Getting info about an existing push: While we were at it, we implemented a way to retrieve information about a push notification. It can be called while it is running or much later, to retrieve status information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are also working on adding a way to cancel a running push in the Boxcar Developer Push Console itself. It will be deployed later in september 2014.&lt;/p&gt;
</content>
  </entry>
