# Integrate push notifications to your applications

Boxcar is a push service that allows developers to integrate push notifications to their applications. It can be integrated in developer's applications through the use of a [SDK](/sdk/), available for [Android](/sdk/android), [Kindle Fire](/sdk/amazon), [Nokia X](/sdk/nokia) and [iOS](/sdk/ios).

Push notifications are typically sent to mobile users when some events occurs on the developer servers / back-end. An HTTPS [publisher API](/api/publisher) is available to allow developer to send notification to either a single device, a single user or a group of users.

<a href="/console/" type="button" class="btn btn-danger">Get Started</a>;T;
I"P
<h1 id="integrate-push-notifications-to-your-applications">Integrate push notifications to your applications</h1>

<p>Boxcar is a push service that allows developers to integrate push notifications to their applications. It can be integrated in developer‚Äôs applications through the use of a <a href="/sdk/">SDK</a>, available for <a href="/sdk/android">Android</a>, <a href="/sdk/amazon">Kindle Fire</a>, <a href="/sdk/nokia">Nokia X</a> and <a href="/sdk/ios">iOS</a>.</p>

<p>Push notifications are typically sent to mobile users when some events occurs on the developer servers / back-end. An HTTPS <a href="/api/publisher">publisher API</a> is available to allow developer to send notification to either a single device, a single user or a group of users.</p>

<p><a href="/console/" type="button" class="btn btn-danger">Get Started</a></p>
