# SDK

Boxcar Developer SDK are used by developers to enable push in their mobile application. The SDK integrates push notification best practices and is the shortest path to get reliable notifications implemented in their mobile application.

Boxcar SDK can be downloaded from [Boxcar management console](https://console.boxcar.io), in the SDK tab.

SDK is currently available for for [Android](/sdk/android), [Kindle Fire](/sdk/amazon), [Nokia X](/sdk/nokia) and [iOS](/sdk/ios).
;T;
I"?
<h1 id="sdk">SDK</h1>

<p>Boxcar Developer SDK are used by developers to enable push in their mobile application. The SDK integrates push notification best practices and is the shortest path to get reliable notifications implemented in their mobile application.</p>

<p>Boxcar SDK can be downloaded from <a href="https://console.boxcar.io">Boxcar management console</a>, in the SDK tab.</p>

<p>SDK is currently available for for <a href="/sdk/android">Android</a>, <a href="/sdk/amazon">Kindle Fire</a>, <a href="/sdk/nokia">Nokia X</a> and <a href="/sdk/ios">iOS</a>.</p>
