    <title type="html">Boxcar iOS SDK 1.0.17</title>
    <published>2014-09-03T22:00:00Z</published>
    <updated>2014-09-03T22:00:00Z</updated>
    <author>
      <name>mremond</name>
      <uri>https://github.com/mremond</uri>
    </author>
    <link rel="alternate" href="http://developer.boxcar.io/blog/2014-09-04-boxcar-ios-sdk-1/" />
    <content type="html">
&lt;p&gt;Boxcar Framework v.1.0.17 make the following changes:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Renamed Boxcar ‚ÄòadvertisingIdentifier‚Äô attribute to the more generic value ‚ÄòdeviceIdentifier‚Äô. It was previously called udid.
This also make the difference with alias more obvious (alias is for user id, deviceIdentifier is for the device id).&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Fix integration and build in iOS XCode Simulator with latest Xcode version.&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;Switch SDK headers to use of modules import (more modern).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The new SDK is available in developer download area.&lt;/p&gt;
